\begin{align*}
121 &= 5 \cdot 24 + 1 \\
24 &= 24 \cdot 1 + 0
\end{align*}
Then, working backwards, we get:
\begin{align*}
1 &= 121 - 5 \cdot 24
\end{align*}
This gives us that $24^{-1} \equiv -5 \equiv 116 \pmod{121}$, as correctly stated in the first answer. The second answer incorrectly states that $24^{-1} \equiv 5 \pmod{121}$.
